= Creating a custom Ingress Controller

When creating an custom Ingress Controller, 

.Prerequisites

* Must have cluster-admin permissions to the cluster
* Create a custom wildcard certificate for the custom domain.
?Do we have a link to this elsewhere...(# oc create secret tls custom-ingress-custom-certs -n openshift-ingress --cert=<certificate.crt> --key=<key.key>)

.Procedure

. Define the ingress controller in a file as template:
+
[source,yaml]
----
# cat custom-ingress-controller.yaml

apiVersion: operator.openshift.io/v1
kind: IngressController
metadata:
name: custom
namespace: openshift-ingress-operator
spec:
defaultCertificate:
    name: custom-ingress-custom-certs
domain: "custom-domain.mycompany.com"
nodePlacement:
    nodeSelector:
    matchLabels:
        ingress-custom-controller: "true"
replicas: 2
status: {}
----

. Set the `spec.domain` to your domain name.
. Label the nodes with the nodeSelecter from the `ingresscontrollers   ` object
. use the secret with the custom wildcare domain defined in `spec.defaultCertificate`.
